Using parallel computing, it is possible to reduce the computation time needed
for generating the data that feeds the g2 estimators.

If you have multiple processor cores at you disposal, you might want to
distribute the computational cost across them.

We offer an option for you to do that by allowing the possibility of dividing
the distribution generation job for the complete set of 4155 sources into
smaller jobs for several subset of sources.

